---

<Base
  title={title}
  description={metaDescription}
  canonical={canonical}
>
  <script slot="schema" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(localBusinessSchema)} />
  <script slot="schema" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(serviceSchema)} />

  <Header slot="header" />

  <div class="container py-6">
    <Breadcrumbs
      items={[
        { label: "Kitchen Fitter Bedworth", href: "/kitchen-fitter-bedworth/" },
      ]}
    />
  </div>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--bg-light);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-5 leading-tight" style="color: var(--navy);">
          Kitchen Fitter Bedworth — Independent Kitchen Installation by Pindi Sahota
        </h1>
        <AnswerBlock
          answer="Pindi Sahota is an independent kitchen fitter serving Bedworth and the CV12 postcode. With 30 years of experience — including the compact galley kitchens typical of Bedworth's post-war housing — he fits kitchens from Wren, Howdens, Magnet, IKEA and every major retailer. Fixed-price quotes guaranteed after a £195 pre-installation survey, credited back on booking."
        />
        <KeyTakeaway points={takeawayPoints} />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Photo Gallery -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6" style="color: var(--navy);">
        Kitchen Installations in Bedworth
      </h2>
      <div class="gallery-grid">
        <figure class="gallery-item">
          <img
            src="/assets/kitchen-fitter/kitchen-fitter-bedworth-grey-shaker-granite-worktop-4032x3024.webp"
            alt="Kitchen fitter Bedworth — grey shaker kitchen with black granite worktop installed in Bedworth, Warwickshire"
            width="4032"
            height="3024"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
            class="gallery-img"
          />
        </figure>
        <figure class="gallery-item">
          <img
            src="/assets/kitchen-fitter/kitchen-fitter-bedworth-white-kitchen-marble-island-warwickshire-3024x4032.webp"
            alt="Kitchen fitter Bedworth — white kitchen with marble island fitted by Install My Kitchen, Warwickshire"
            width="3024"
            height="4032"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
            class="gallery-img"
          />
        </figure>
        <figure class="gallery-item">
          <img
            src="/assets/kitchen-fitter/kitchen-fitter-bedworth-white-handleless-black-granite-kitchen-2448x3264.webp"
            alt="Kitchen fitter Bedworth — white handleless kitchen with black granite worktop installed in CV12"
            width="2448"
            height="3264"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
            class="gallery-img"
          />
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 1: Independent vs Retailer Fitters -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--bg-light);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--navy);">
          Independent Kitchen Fitter vs Retailer Fitter — What's the Difference?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          When you buy a kitchen from a large retailer, they will often offer installation as part of the package. On paper this sounds simple — but the fitters working under retailer schemes are contractors incentivised to work quickly to the retailer's standard, not yours. If something goes wrong, you are caught between the retailer's customer service team and a fitter who is already on to the next job.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          An independent fitter like Pindi Sahota works directly for you. There is no middleman, no call-centre complaints process, and no pressure to rush. He visits your home to carry out a full pre-installation survey, builds a fixed-price quote based on the actual conditions in your kitchen, and then carries out the work himself. If a problem arises — a wall that is not plumb, a floor that needs levelling, a cabinet that arrived with transit damage — he deals with it on the spot rather than logging it for a head office review that may come weeks later.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Independent fitting also means genuine flexibility. Pindi fits kitchens from every retailer and manufacturer. You are free to shop wherever offers the best kitchen for your budget — you do not need to buy from a retailer just to access their installation service.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          For Bedworth homeowners who want the job done properly, by a single experienced tradesperson who is accountable to them, independent fitting is almost always the better choice.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Why Bedworth Homeowners Choose Pindi -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--navy);">
          Why Bedworth Homeowners Choose Pindi Sahota
        </h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Pindi Sahota has been fitting kitchens professionally for 30 years. He is based at 242 Hollyfast Road, Coundon, Coventry CV6 2AH — approximately 8 miles south of Bedworth — and serves the whole of the CV12 postcode area as a matter of routine.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Bedworth's housing stock reflects the town's industrial history. Built largely during the colliery and ribbon-weaving era of the 1950s and 1970s, the majority of properties are post-war semi-detached and terraced houses with compact kitchen footprints. Galley layouts — where units run along one or both sides of a narrow room — are extremely common, and many have lower-than-average ceiling heights that present real technical challenges: wall units must be cut precisely to avoid conflicts with ceiling timbers, extraction routes need to be planned carefully in restricted ceiling voids, and tall larder towers require precise scribing to the room's geometry.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          This is exactly the type of work where experience matters most. Fitting a 20-unit open-plan kitchen in a new-build is technically straightforward. Fitting a 12-unit galley in a 1960s Bedworth terrace, where the floor is not level, the ceiling is 2.1 metres at its lowest point, and the extraction must route through a void that was never designed for it, requires a different level of skill and problem-solving. Pindi has worked in these conditions throughout his career.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          He covers the whole of Bedworth including Exhall, Ash Green, Bulkington, Goodyears End, Hawkesbury, and Longford, as well as the surrounding area across north Warwickshire. Call <a href="tel:07399651836" class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--teal);">07399 651836</a> to discuss your project.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: The Survey-First Process -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--bg-light);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--navy);">
          The Survey-First Process — How It Works
        </h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Every kitchen fitting project begins with a pre-installation survey, carried out by Pindi personally. The survey costs £195 and is credited back in full if you go ahead with the installation. It is not a sales visit — it is a working appointment that produces a detailed, accurate quote for the real job.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          During the survey, Pindi takes precise room measurements, checks ceiling heights and wall angles, inspects existing plumbing and electrics routes, reviews your kitchen plan and elevation drawings, and identifies any work that will need to happen before or alongside the installation — plastering, floor levelling, electrics, gas, or tiling. In Bedworth's older properties, this step is particularly valuable: extraction routing in compact ceiling voids and levelling on uneven concrete floors are common requirements that must be planned for in advance, not discovered on installation day.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          After the survey you receive a written, fixed-price quote. The price does not change unless you change the scope of work. There are no surprises on completion day, no additional charges for complications that should have been spotted in advance.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Survey appointments are typically available within two weeks. To book, call <a href="tel:07399651836" class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--teal);">07399 651836</a> or visit the <a href="/survey/" class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--teal);">survey booking page</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Retailers -->
  <section class="section">
